pull_request.title: Speed up ARM jobs in CI
pull_request.body: Our ARM jobs currently compile liboqs in an emulated environment. With this PR they will cross compile from the x86_64 host and only use emulation to run the tests. This should speed up the ARM jobs significantly. It might take some trial and error to get it working well.

pull_request.title: PQC integration into the 8.x branch.
pull_request.body:
Integrate PQ-only and hybrid key exchange and authentication from OQS into the 8.x branch. Implements the [draft-kampanakis-curdle-pq-ssh-00](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-kampanakis-curdle-pq-ssh/) spec. For hybrid KEX, we follow the design of the [ntru-x25519](https://github.com/openssh/openssh-portable/blob/master/kexsntrup4591761x25519.c) integration currently in OpenSSH.

Here are the steps to complete the work (might result in multiple PRs).

KEX tasks:
- [x] Implement PQ-only KEX with one alg
- [x] Implement hybrid KEX with one alg
- [x] Extend support to all security levels (enabled frodo L1/3/5 + ecdh hybrid)
- [ ] Use templates to support all OQS KEM algs (grep for `FIXMEOQS: TEMPLATE`)
- [ ] Add CI testing
- [ ] Update docs (README, etc.)

Auth tasks
- [x] Implement PQ-only auth with one alg
- [x] Implement hybrid auth with one alg
- [x] Extend support to all security levels (enabled dilithium L1/L3/L5, +L1 rsa hybrid, +L1/3/5 ecdsa hybrid)
- [ ] Use templates to support all OQS sig algs (grep for `FIXMEOQS: TEMPLATE`)
- [ ] Add CI testing
- [ ] Update docs (README, etc.)
